1
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:10,000
[Episode 7: Who'd Tell a Sworn Enemy Secrets?]

2
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:15,711
Scallions and ginger
remove the fishy smell, right?

3
00:01:15,711 --> 00:01:16,359
Right.

4
00:01:16,359 --> 00:01:18,240
<i>As fragrant flowers attract butterflies,</i>

5
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,599
<i>we can win</i>

6
00:01:19,599 --> 00:01:21,200
<i>her heart with our charm</i>

7
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,790
<i>and make her regret.</i>

8
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:24,136
Right.

9
00:01:24,136 --> 00:01:27,040
For beginners, steaming is easier.

10
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:28,920
I seldom cook mackerel.

11
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,000
I'll show you first.

12
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,160
If the dish is fine,

13
00:01:31,160 --> 00:01:32,839
I'll teach you step by step.

14
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,813
What's wrong... with your voice?

15
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,179
Nothing.

16
00:01:47,443 --> 00:01:48,680
What about this one?

17
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:51,917
For pan-frying.
Let's see which one tastes better.

18
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:00,926
It's bitter.

19
00:02:01,879 --> 00:02:04,640
Is my mackerel... stale?

20
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,551
Try this one.

21
00:02:30,639 --> 00:02:32,360
Lower the heat.

22
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,639
Fry twice?

23
00:02:33,639 --> 00:02:35,240
This is called refrying.

24
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,599
It removes excess oil

25
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:38,400
and makes the skin crispier.

26
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,335
It's still bitter.

27
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:08,320
Only fresh fish has such a gill tone.

28
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:11,132
So... it's not due to fish?

29
00:03:16,159 --> 00:03:17,760
Let's try another method.

30
00:03:17,760 --> 00:03:19,046
Okay.

31
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:44,120
Telephone charges,

32
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,080
board expenses,

33
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:48,943
ingredient costs for improving the recipe...

34
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:52,149
I've been spending a lot lately.

35
00:03:54,479 --> 00:03:56,800
<i>Despite my savings,</i>

36
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:59,069
<i>it can't last long.</i>

37
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:03,241
<i>If I receive some incomes...</i>

38
00:04:03,831 --> 00:04:05,320
<i>Remember to prepare your resignation.</i>

39
00:04:05,320 --> 00:04:07,520
<i>Hand over to the new foreman
before you leave next week.</i>

40
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,039
<i>We've discussed it internally.</i>

41
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,479
<i>Zhao Qi Ming remains as supervisor.</i>

42
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:11,797
<i>You're dismissed.</i>

43
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:17,000
<i>Since I'm dismissed,</i>

44
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,010
<i>I should at least get my advance back.</i>

45
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,015
<i>But...</i>

46
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:26,497
<i>It's really hard to ask.</i>

47
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,759
<i>I just got back from the market.</i>

48
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:33,012
<i>You can come over.</i>

49
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:34,745
<i>Right away.</i>

50
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,890
Also bitter?

51
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,600
Only three days left. It's too late.

52
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,240
I can't ask her directly

53
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:12,319
why my fish tastes bitter, can I?

54
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,800
Why not?

55
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,440
She and my mom are sworn enemies.

56
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,516
Who'd tell a sworn enemy secrets?

57
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,480
Duan Yu and Mu Rong Fu,

58
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,839
Zhang Wu Ji and Zhao Min,

59
00:05:22,839 --> 00:05:25,160
Master Yi Deng and Qiu Qian Ren.

60
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,040
Are you asking me?

61
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,920
Not until I came to your diner did I know that,

62
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,879
though our dishes look similar,

63
00:05:34,879 --> 00:05:36,040
they taste

64
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,759
quite different.

65
00:05:37,759 --> 00:05:39,040
Sorry for

66
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,761
misunderstanding you.

67
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,597
He doesn't smoke.

68
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,125
I quit.

69
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,879
Could you please tell me

70
00:06:02,879 --> 00:06:05,800
why my mackerel tastes bitter?

71
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,519
She and I are rivals.

72
00:06:07,519 --> 00:06:08,759
Who'd tell a rival

73
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:10,120
her trade secrets?

74
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,600
Duan Yu and Mu Rong Fu,

75
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,880
Zhang Wu Ji and Zhao Min,

76
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:14,638
Master Yi Deng and...

77
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:16,620
and...

78
00:06:16,620 --> 00:06:18,280
Qiu Qian Ren.

79
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,640
That's right!

80
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:21,319
Why should I help her?

81
00:06:21,319 --> 00:06:23,320
I can be your cashier, washer,

82
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,800
and business planner!

83
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,966
You can't even figure out your mom.

84
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,923
Auntie Qiu!

85
00:06:28,923 --> 00:06:30,680
That's why I came to consult you.

86
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:33,000
You held me when I was little.

87
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,839
I have dozens of pounds of lard in the kitchen,

88
00:06:34,839 --> 00:06:35,880
but no time to render it.

89
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,985
I can do it! I can learn.

90
00:07:08,935 --> 00:07:09,607
Hello?

91
00:07:09,607 --> 00:07:11,192
<i>Hello, Nan Feng.</i>

92
00:07:11,192 --> 00:07:13,000
With a fixed budget,

93
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,120
your refusal to pay me

94
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:16,442
is understandable.

95
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:18,800
I only want my credit.

96
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,394
Can't you even do that?

97
00:07:20,394 --> 00:07:21,720
<i>Nan Feng,</i>

98
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,200
<i>don't be so petty, okay?</i>

99
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,720
<i>Everyone has a tough time.</i>

100
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:27,327
I won't continue without a contract.

101
00:07:27,327 --> 00:07:29,600
<i>No, no, no. To be honest,</i>

102
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,000
<i>it's not that I won't write,</i>

103
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,560
<i>but that my kid is undergoing a surgery.</i>

104
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:36,020
<i>I really can't get away.</i>

105
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,079
<i>His left ear has sudden deafness.</i>

106
00:07:40,079 --> 00:07:41,120
<i>You're his mom.</i>

107
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,287
<i>If you don't take care of him, who will?</i>

108
00:07:43,287 --> 00:07:45,519
<i>So? He isn't your son?</i>

109
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:48,469
<i>You ignore him after divorce?</i>

110
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:51,720
<i>Well, if you don't take care, neither do I.</i>

111
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,779
<i>Up to you.</i>

112
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,240
<i>Let's go home.</i>

113
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,418
<i>Is it my fault?</i>

114
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,746
<i>- Who cares, who takes care, okay?
- I won't take it seriously.</i>

115
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,050
Send me the requirements.

116
00:08:10,050 --> 00:08:11,319
<i>Okay, okay, okay!</i>

117
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:13,097
<i>Right away, right away.</i>

118
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:20,280
[Qiuping Diner]

119
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,000
That's all?

120
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,306
That's all.

121
00:08:35,279 --> 00:08:36,440
Thanks for your efforts.

122
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,840
Tired? Wipe your sweat.

123
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,118
Thank you.

124
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,879
Mackerel has a small gallbladder.

125
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:45,240
It's easy to break.

126
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:47,360
If broken, it certainly tastes bitter.

127
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,418
So that's the reason.

128
00:08:49,418 --> 00:08:50,640
Cut open the fish belly,

129
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:51,960
pinch the front of the internal organs

130
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,240
and pull it out.

131
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:54,960
But you must be gentle.

132
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,168
Your mom taught me this.

133
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,101
I really quit.

134
00:09:03,101 --> 00:09:05,581
Smoke less. It hurts.

135
00:09:06,639 --> 00:09:08,240
Auntie Qiu,

136
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,644
why did you disconnect from my mom?

137
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,320
It's the last day.

138
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,040
Have you come up with a signature dish?

139
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,473
You're ill.

140
00:09:30,279 --> 00:09:31,720
The taste changed.

141
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,360
The customers left.

142
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,840
Auntie Qiu noticed you couldn't taste,

143
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,560
insisted on your checkup,

144
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:39,318
tasted and seasoned dishes for you, but you!

145
00:09:39,318 --> 00:09:41,480
You chased her away.
The customers followed her.

146
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,632
And you're here sulking with her.

147
00:09:46,554 --> 00:09:47,560
But...

148
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,520
But she added to the pot

149
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,159
without my permission.

150
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:53,039
Who's to blame if anyone gets sick?

151
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,840
This doesn't mean you should kick her out.

152
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,427
That's my bad temper.

153
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,720
Were it not for my bad temper,

154
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:02,186
we'd be bullied as usual!

155
00:10:08,293 --> 00:10:09,478
[Nanwan First People's Hospital]
Mom.

156
00:10:09,478 --> 00:10:11,480
I really want to help you.

157
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,640
Alright.

158
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,960
Just return

159
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,399
and find a decent job.

160
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:17,680
So that the neighbors won't pry.

161
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,312
Aren't you tired?

162
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,600
You lie,

163
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,329
and try to cover it alone throughout your life.

164
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:31,119
You can't hide the truth forever.

165
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:33,840
I'd rather live this way.

166
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,519
I'd rather lie throughout my life.

167
00:10:35,519 --> 00:10:37,280
I'd rather try to hide the truth.

168
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,125
I can help you!

169
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,679
I can lie for you throughout your life.

170
00:10:40,679 --> 00:10:42,120
I can help you hide the truth.

171
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,185
Well, that's enough.

172
00:10:43,185 --> 00:10:44,840
Without Wang Qiu Ping's skills,

173
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,879
you needn't consider

174
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,679
taking care of the diner or what.

175
00:10:47,679 --> 00:10:49,756
Now go, go. Just go.

176
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,254
Nice to meet you, Auntie.

177
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,465
Xiang Nan Feng,

178
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,080
my friend.

179
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,477
High school classmate.

180
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:31,940
Let me do it.

181
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,640
She said

182
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:37,021
it only counts if I do it myself.

183
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,737
She's not here.

184
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:44,056
I know that with your help I can do better.

185
00:11:44,679 --> 00:11:45,917
But...

186
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:48,859
At least I don't want to lie to her.

187
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:34,837
Thank you.

188
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,628
Go for it.

189
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,784
The gallbladder burst
when you cleaned the fish, right?

190
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,519
Shouldn't you express something

191
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:03,639
like you're touched by me?

192
00:13:03,639 --> 00:13:06,240
With your culinary skills,
you'd starve if you leave home.

193
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:08,120
At least learn something before you leave.

194
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,555
Got it.

195
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:14,727
Thank you for supporting Xi Zhou.

196
00:13:14,727 --> 00:13:16,608
Come by whenever you want.

197
00:13:20,159 --> 00:13:21,484
I will, Auntie.

198
00:13:23,156 --> 00:13:24,581
Auntie, I have to go.

199
00:13:24,581 --> 00:13:25,976
- Okay.
- I'll walk you out.

200
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:27,757
Okay.

201
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,000
If you're happy to stay,

202
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,240
why don't you tell her?

203
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,020
That's too mushy.
